  "body": "\r\n**üíª Environment**\r\n\r\nTruffle v5.1.42 (core: 5.1.42)\r\nNode v13.6.0\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nMy ERC-20 token uses solc version 0.6.0 and imports the library of openzeppelin version 3.0.2 with the following compilers info.\r\n```\r\ncompilers: {\r\n    solc: {\r\n      version: \"^0.6.2\",    // Fetch exact version from solc-bin (default: truffle's version)\r\n      docker: false,        // Use \"0.5.1\" you've installed locally with docker (default: false)\r\n      settings: {          // See the solidity docs for advice about optimization and evmVersion\r\n        optimizer: {\r\n          enabled: true,\r\n          runs: 200\r\n        },\r\n        evmVersion: \"byzantium\"\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n**üî¢ Code to reproduce bug**\r\n\r\nCompile a code which imports `@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/Address.sol` version 3.0.2 and it shows the below errors\r\n\r\n```\r\n@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/Address.sol:33:32: TypeError: The \"extcodehash\" instruction is only available for Constantinople-compatible VMs  (you are currently compiling for \"byzantium\").\r\n        assembly { codehash := extcodehash(account) }\r\n                               ^---------^\r\n,@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/Address.sol:33:20: DeclarationError: Variable count does not match number of values (1 vs. 0)\r\n        assembly { codehash := extcodehash(account) }\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich solc version should I use for compilers?",
